<br>
I. You cannot post more then 2 weeks ahead of the start of the first day of the raid. For the Brell Board purposes, a day begins at 12:00:00 AM PST. A sky raid may claim between one and three consecutive days in the plane.  Any post will be deleted if it breaks any portion of this rule. Board time will be used to determine this. <br>
<br>
II. Do not reserve sky again before your first raid is over. The second post of 2 will be deleted. <br>
<br>
III. Non raid specific or inappropriate posts in the raid forums will be deleted. Only post intended raids, there is a Raids: Discussion forum for any questions, comments or concerns.<br>
<br>
IV. Old posts will be deleted the day following the last day of the raid. If a raid was posted for the 8th through the 10th then the post for that raid will be deleted sometime on the 11th.<br>
<br>
V.  Do not post multiple times for the same date.  If more than one person from a guild posts a reservation for a date, only the earlier one will be accepted.  If a person posts multiple times for the same date, all posts beyond the first will be deleted.<br>
<br>
VI.  Do not post reservations for both Hate &amp; Fear on the same day.  If you post to both planes, only the earlier reservation will be accepted, and all subsequent posts will be deleted.<br>
<br>
VII.  If you are waiting on a roll off for a date, you MAY post for another date.  However, if you get that later date, your forfiet your chance to roll on the earlier date.  Ie: Guild A ties with Guild B for Saturday.  Guild A signs up for Sunday, and gets it.  Guild B then gets Saturday, and guild A gets Sunday.<br>
<br>
ADMIN NOTE:  Clarified the starting time for our definition of when a day begins, since not every seemed to know this. <p><BR>
